      "Another solution would be to have `.nth( x, default_value)`\r\n\r\nIn case of an \"index out of bounds\" error:\r\n- If `default_value` is not defined, we throw the error\r\n- If `default_value` is defined, we return this value instead of an error.\r\n\r\nSo @coffeemug query would look like\r\n```javascript\r\nr.table('characters').map(function (character) {\r\n  return r.table('tv_shows').filter({ name: character('show') }).nth(0, {}).merge(character);\r\n}).run()\r\n```"
